"Holy Lands of Korin"\n\nYou continue along paths tread by the many hundreds of worshipers in ancient past.\n\nAside the trodden path, grass blows in the breeze. This way has remained peaceful, though it shares its perimeter with the shaded woods in which threatening creatures must dwell. You have, up to this point, made it a mission to avoid such places.<<if $ornateLunarScope == 0>>\n\nLight glints off a reflective object in the grass. It may be wise to [[investigate further.|Holy Lands of Korin 1][$ornateLunarScope = 1]]\n\n<<else>>\n\n//Acquired Ornate Lunar Scope//\n\n<<endif>>Just beyond, the ramparts of the Eastern Capital distort the nearly constant wall of greenery that has absorbed the view for itself.\n\n[[Enter the gates of the Eastern Capital.|Eastern Capital 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]

"Buried Study"\n\nYou are in a room with literature surrounding you.\n\nThe texts detail secrets of Alandriule that have long been forgotten.\n\n[[Read on.|Ending Buried Study]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
.passage .header {\n background-image: [img[Lake Anduril]];\n}
You ascend the rocky mountain path.\n\nAt a clearing, you see a beast with a single, red, glowing eye in the center of its head. It stands perfectly still.\n\n[[Move toward it.|Path to Fire Mountain 3]]\n\n[[Back away from it.|Path to Fire Mountain 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
As you approach the beast, its gaze never leaves you.\n\nSuddenly you are surrounded by numerous similar beasts. As they stare at you, you can feel your sense of self diminishing.\n\n<<if $mirrorGem == 1>>[[Use Mirror Gem.|Ending Fire Mountain]]<<else>>You are turned to stone by the beasts. Your journey was not yet complete.<<endif>>\n\n<<if $mirrorGem == 1>>[[Inventory|Inventory]]<<endif>>
"Path to Fire Mountain"\n\nYou are at the base of the Fire Mountain. The atmosphere is dense with the toxic ash of the Dragon's awakening.\n\nBirds and reptiles have been turned to stone and now decorate this path. You spend time reading about the history of the Fire Dragon, and of the Ice Dragon. They once guarded a great castle together, until the King inside went mad. The Dragon's were split on what to do with him and his kingdom, and they spent a century in combat. The flames burnt Alandriule into nothingness. The ice kept Alandriule in the dark.\n\nWith no way out, you spend the rest of your life here, reading accounts of distant history.\n\n//You have seen more than most. By my blessing you have achieved wisdom of ages. Fear not, Lyn.//\n\nFin.

Horizons
.passage .header {\n background-image: [img[Tower]];\n}
A flash of bright light emits from the beasts. The Mirror Gem reflects the light in all directions, turning the beasts to stone. However, you are not able to evade their gaze let alone the Mirror Gem's reflection, and you are petrified as well.\n\nThe path will remain pacified, but yours and the beasts stone graves will mark it.\n\n//You have my blessing. Your honorable death will be seen by many, as well the gazes of Basilisks shall never leave yours, and they will never forget because of it, Lyn.//\n\nFin.

"Desert of Conane"\n\nYou travel across the desert in an effort to reach the coastal town.\n\nWith a loud roar, a three story high sand worm bursts from the ground. The floor beneath you begins to drift inward towards the worm. You are encased in sand and fall into the spiralling pit.\n\n[[...|The Undersea 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]

"The Undersea"\n\nYou are underneath the desert.\n\nA cavern has formed here over centuries. Teal rock formations surround you. Most of this area is too crystallite to navigate. A single passage extends into a small alcove.\n\n[[Go inside.|Buried Study]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
The altar glows brightly and hums gently. You feel as if every particle of your being is separating into oblivion. You leave the realm of consciousness.\n\nThe bay receives a blessing. The violet recedes, and hardens into crystal. Toxicity is cleansed from the water, and sparkling, blue life returns to its color.\n\n//You will remain here at this altar. Your body a vessel for the poisons you've undone. A statue of violet crystal, kneeling before me, you receive my blessing, Lyn.//\n\nFin.
<<if $left == 0>>"Eastern Capital"\n\nYou enter a town of moderate population.\n\nIts natural boundaries have made this place a slight obscurity. In some places in town, it is possible to see the rampantly growing branches and roots of nearby trees peaking over and even joining constitution with the town walls.\n\nYour business here is limited. It is rare for civilians to converse with one fully clad in armor like yourself. Even rarer if the word is you are a sellsword. The best course of action here is to pass through without residential confrontation.\n\n[[Leave town.|Eastern Capital 1][$left = 1]]<<endif>><<if $left == 1>>You take one last moment to recognize that this journey will be your final duty. You must decide where to begin.\n\nThe South Gate leads to a section of the Lurk Wood that surrounds this place. Few have ventured beyond the immediate surroundings in this direction.\n[[Leave through the South Gate.|South Lurk Wood 1]]\n\nThe North gate leads to a section of the Lurk Wood that surrounds this place. The Northernmost mountains of the mainland can be seen beyond.\n[[Leave through the North Gate.|North Lurk Wood 1]]\n\nThe West Gate leads to a walled section of forest that provides a straight shot to the mainland.\n[[Leave through the West Gate.|Forest Walls 1]]<<endif>>\n\n[[Go back.|Holy Lands of Korin 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
The canopy forms a ceiling above you. A giant spider glides down in front of you. Many others follow suit. Their eyes are lit up like flames.\n\n<<if $doomStrawberry == 0>><<if $attack == 0>>[[Attack!|North Lurk Wood 2][$attack += 1]]<<else>>You cleave several of them into pieces, but they keep coming.\n\n[[Keep hacking away...|North Lurk Wood 2][$attack += 1]]\n\n[[Run through!|North Lurk Wood 3]]<<endif>><<else>><<if $usedDoomStrawberry == 0>>[[Use Doom Strawberry.|North Lurk Wood 2][$usedDoomStrawberry = 1]]<<else>>A loud tick freezes all the spiders in their tracks. Some fall from the canopy with a thud. They won't bother you for a while.<<if $spidersFlame == 0>>\n\n[[Take one of their eyes.|North Lurk Wood 2][$spidersFlame = 1]]<<else if $spidersFlame > 0>>\n\n//Spider's Flame Acquired//<<endif>><<endif>><<else if $attack > 3>>\n\n[[Dash through an opening!|North Lurk Wood 2]]<<endif>><<if $usedDoomStrawberry == 1>>\n\n[[Move on.|North Lurk Wood 3]]<<endif>>\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]

The bird lifts you into the air and takes off.\n\nYou see the greenery zipping by. The bird takes you over the edge of the highlands. It soars over the bay.\n\nFor a moment things are calm as you glide through the air. You see a dark mass of birds in the distance cover the forest in fear.\n\nThe bird swoops down near an old merchant post on the Red Mountains. It drops you off, then flies off on its own.\n\n[[Move on.|Path to Fire Mountain 2]]
"Tower of Korin"\n\nYou leave the Tower of Korin with renewed purpose.\n\nThe base of the tower is a calm field surrounded on one side by dense woods and on the other by endless plains. This is the secluded pocket of serenity you frequented in between duties. You sat here overlooking the shore but never knowing Her acceptance and being fine with that. You are used to being alone.\n\nThe path to the Eastern Capital is through the grassy fields before you.\n\n[[Onward.|Holy Lands of Korin 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory][$luna += 1]]

"Alfone Ruins"\n\nAncient ruins surround you.\n\nThe geographic emptiness has left the area to rot in peace.\n\n[[Move on.|Ruins of Alfone 2]]\n\n[[Go back.|Highlands of Korin 3]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
You are within a dark passageway that ascends the ruins.<<if $tonalStone == 0>><<if $examined == 0>>\n\nSeveral alcoves present themselves to you. [[Examine them.|Ruins of Alfone 2][$examined = 1]]<<else>>\n\nAn ancient altar is hidden away in the dark. A stone sits by it, emitting a soothing sound.\n\n[[Take it.|Ruins of Alfone 2][$tonalStone = 1]]<<endif>><<else>>\n\n//Acquired Tonal Stone//<<endif>>\n\n[[Move on.|Ruins of Alfone 3]]\n\n[[Go back.|Ruins of Alfone 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
You reach the peak of your ascent. You overlook the Bay of Alfone, which shares a coast with the mountain from which the dragon has awakened.\n\nSmoke billows into the dark clouds in the distance. A dark, violet sand drifts into the bay beneath you. The altar before you promises salvation.\n\n[[Step up to the altar.|Ending Bay of Alfone]]\n\n[[Go back.|Ruins of Alfone 2]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]

"Forest Walls"\n\nYou are in a narrow passage with walls extending higher than the trees.\n\nThe dark walls are nearly smooth and mostly featureless save for their age.\n\n[[Move on.|Forest Walls 2]]\n\n[[Go back.|Eastern Capital 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
"Korin Highlands"\n\nYou are amidst lush hills. The ground is moist, but firm.\n\nMany birds are wandering about high above.\n\n[[Move on.|Highlands of Korin 2]]\n\n[[Go back.|South Lurk Wood 3]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
You are finding your footing on somewhat steep and rocky hills.<<if $birdFlight == 0>><<if $approached == 0>>\n\nA giant pigeon sits in its nest not far from you.\n\n[[Approach it.|Highlands of Korin 2][$approached = 1]]<<else>><<if $tonalStone == 0>>\n\nThe pigeon immediately flies away from you.<<else>>\n\nThe pigeon sits calmly.\n\n[[Get on.|Flight][|$birdFlight = 1]]<<endif>><<endif>>\n\n<<endif>>[[Move on.|Highlands of Korin 3]]\n\n[[Go back.|Highlands of Korin 1]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
You are atop a natural barrier of hills.\n\nBelow you, ancient ruins stand tall as if never disturbed. Far beyond, the piercing glow of the Fire Mountains spews blackness into the air.\n\n[[Move on.|Ruins of Alfone 1]]\n\n[[Go back.|Highlands of Korin 2]]\n\n[[Inventory|Inventory]]
